tish Rail Class 230|230]]<ref name=\"servimp\">{{cite web |title=Service Improvements |url=https://gov.wales/docs/cabinetstatements/2018/180604serviceimprovementsen.pdf |website=Transport for Wales |publisher=[[Welsh Government]] |access-date=4 June 2018}}</ref>\n|[[File:D-Train-203001-Approach-Honeybourne-P1410129.jpg|120x120px|alt=]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" align=\"center\" |[[Diesel-electric multiple unit|DEMU]]\n|align=center|60\n|align=center|97\n|align=center|3\n|align=center|5\n|\n* [[Borderlands line|<small>Borderlands line</small>]]\n* [[Conwy Valley line|<small>Conwy Valley line</small>]]\n* <small> Chester-Crewe </small>\n| align=\"center\" |2019-20\n| align=\"center\" |2020\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Stadler FLIRT]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[British Rail Class 231|231]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |\n| align=\"center\" |100\n| align=\"center\" |161\n| align=\"center\" |4\n| align=\"center\" |11\n|\n* <small>[[Maesteg Line|Maesteg-Cardiff Central-Cheltenham Spa]] (from 2022)</small>\n* <small>[[Ebbw Valley Railway|Cardiff Central/Newport-Ebbw Vale]] (from 2022)</small>\n|align=center|2021-22\n| align=\"center\" |2022\n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" |[[File:TfW Class 231.png|alt=|820x820px]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"11\" |Bi-mode multiple units\n|-\n|\n|[[British Rail Class 769|769/0 & 769/4 ''Flex'']]\n|[[File:British Rail Class 769.jpg|120x120px|alt=]]\n| align=\"center\" |[[Electro-diesel locomotive|BMU]]\n|align=center|100\n|align=center|161\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|9\n|{{small|Valley Lines}}\n|align=center|2017-19\n|align=center|2020{{refn|group=nb|Class 319/4 units were initially built between 1987 and 1988}}\n|-\n! colspan=\"11\" |Tri-mode multiple units<ref name=WhatSE/>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Stadler FLIRT]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[British Rail Class 756|756]]\n|rowspan=3|\n|rowspan=3 align=center|TMU\n|rowspan=2 align=center|100\n|rowspan=2 align=center|161\n|align=center|3\n|align=center|7\n|{{small|Services between Caerphilly/Coryton to Penarth}}<ref name=Overview>{{cite web |title=AMs WB Overview Presentation vJP AM |url=http://www.keolisamey.cymru/media/1046/ams-wb-overview-presentation.pdf |website=KeolisAmey Wales |publisher=KeolisAmey Wales |access-date=5 June 2018}}{{dead link|date=February 2019}}</ref><ref name=CVLStock>{{cite web |title=CVL Rolling Stock List |url=https://tfw.gov.wales/sites/default/files/documents/Copy%20of%20Sched%201.6_Table%202d.pdf |website=Transport for Wales |publisher=Transport for Wales |access-date=14 August 2019}}</ref>\n|rowspan=2 align=center|TBC\n|rowspan=2 align=center|2023\n|-\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|17\n|{{small|Services between Rhymney to Barry Island/Bridgend via VoG}}<ref name=Overview/><ref name=CVLStock/>\n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" |[[File:TfW Class 756 3 Car w-pantograph.png|alt=|667x667px]]\n[[File:TfW Class 756 4 Car w-pantograph.png|alt=|825x825px]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"11\" |Tram-trains\n|-\n|[[Stadler Citylink]]\n|[[British Rail Class 398|398]]\n|\n| align=\"center\" |[[Tram-train]]\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" |TBC\n| align=\"center\" |3\n| align=\"center\" |36\n|{{small|Services to Treherbert, Aberdare and Merthyr Tydfil}}<ref name=\"WhatSE\" />\n| align=\"center\" |TBC\n| align=\"center\" |2022\u201323\n|-\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=nb}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website}}\n\n{{Commons category}}\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Arriva Trains Wales]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Operator of [[Wales & Borders franchise]]\n|years=2018\u20132033}}\n{{s-aft|after=incumbent}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{South Wales Metro}}\n{{UK TOCs|current}}\n{{Keolis}}\n\n[[Category:Keolis]]\n[[Category:Railway companies established in 2018]]\n[[Category:Railway companies of Wales]]\n[[Category:Train operating companies in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:2018 establishments in Wales]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in Shropshire]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in Wales]]\n[[Category:Transport in Cardiff]]\n[[Category:Transport operators of Wales]]\n", "name_user": "Davey2010", "label": "safe",